Introduction
Brown long-eared bats are medium-sized. The ears are nearly as long as the body but not
always obvious: when at rest they curl their ears back like ramsâ€™ horns, or tuck them away completely under their wings leaving only the pointed inner lobe of the ear (the tragus) visible.

Vital statistics
Head & body length: 37mm - 52mm
Forearm length: 34mm - 42mm
Wingspan: 230mm - 285mm
Weight: 6g - 12g
Thumb: More than 6.2mm (in comparison with grey long-eared)
Tragus: Greatest width less than 5.5m (in comparison with grey long-eared)
Colour: Adults have light brown fur, pale underneath; juveniles greyish -beware confusion with grey long-eared!